-- filename: int_deduped_billing.sql
```sql
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- filename: int_subscription_monthly.sql
```sql
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        b.event_month,
        s.plan_id,
        u.company_id,
        s.status,
        b.amount,
        p.tier,
        c.industry
    FROM {{ ref('int_deduped_billing') }} b
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
        ON s.subscription_id = b.subscription_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_users') }} u
        ON u.user_id = s.user_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_companies') }} c
        ON c.company_id = u.company_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
        ON p.plan_id = s.plan_id
)
SELECT
    event_month AS month,
    COALESCE(tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
    COALESCE(industry, '(unknown)') AS industry,
    status,
    amount
FROM source
```

-- filename: fct_subscription_metrics.sql
```sql
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        month,
        tier,
        industry,
        subscription_id,
        user_id,
        amount,
        status
    FROM {{ ref('int_subscription_monthly') }}
)
SELECT
    month,
    tier,
    industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    COALESCE(SUM(amount), 0) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS unique_users
FROM source
WHERE status = 'active'
GROUP BY
    month,
    tier,
    industry
ORDER BY
    month DESC,
    tier,
    industry
